First expand and collect like terms:

\[
(v+1)(v-5)-4=0 
\;\Longrightarrow\;
v^2-5v+v-5-4=0
\;\Longrightarrow\;
v^2-4v-9=0.
\]

Now apply the quadratic formula \(v=\frac{-b\pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}\) with \(a=1\), \(b=-4\), \(c=-9\):

\[
v=\frac{-(-4)\pm\sqrt{(-4)^2-4\cdot1\cdot(-9)}}{2\cdot1}
=\frac{4\pm\sqrt{16+36}}{2}
=\frac{4\pm\sqrt{52}}{2}
=\frac{4\pm2\sqrt{13}}{2}
=2\pm\sqrt{13}.
\]

Hence the solutions are 
\[
\boxed{v=2+\sqrt{13}\quad\text{or}\quad v=2-\sqrt{13}}.
\]
